text: The rainforest rocket frog (Silverstoneia flotator) is a frog. It lives in Costa Rica and Panama. Scientists think it could live in Nicaragua too. Scientists are not sure that this is one species of frog. They think it might really be a few species. This frog lives on the ground in rainforests. This frog moves during the day. People have seen this frog between 10 and 865 meters above sea level. It lives near streams that have rocks in them. People have seen the frog in forests that have been cut down and are growing back. The female frog lays eggs in dead leaves on the ground. After the eggs hatch, the male frog carries the tadpoles streams. Scientists believe this frog is not in danger of dying out because it lives in a large place and it is good at living in places that human beings have changed. It is in some danger because human beings cut down forests to make farms, get wood to build with, and make towns. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Silverstoneia flotator
